        <section>
          <h2>Project Summary</h2>
          <p>JalTantra is an IoT-powered irrigation project integrating soil moisture sensors, weather APIs, a predictive ML model and AWS IoT Core. It reduced water usage by ~30% in trials and won recognition at SPPU and Smart India Hackathon.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Architecture & Components</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Hardware: Raspberry Pi, soil moisture sensors, relay modules</li>
            <li>Edge Software: Python scripts for sensor reading and local decision logic</li>
            <li>ML Model: Predictive model to decide irrigation schedule based on sensor data and weather inputs</li>
            <li>Cloud: AWS IoT Core for device management and data streaming</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Results & Lessons</h2>
          <p>In-field analysis showed a 30% drop in water usage where the system was deployed. Important lessons: robust sensor calibration, handling noisy streams, and designing fallback behavior for connectivity loss.</p>
        </section>

